      <description>
        
          
            &lt;p&gt;Arch Linux is extremely well documented so I highly recommend to read the &lt;a href=&#34;https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Installation_guide&#34;&gt;Arch installation guide&lt;/a&gt;.
This guide installs the Gnome desktop environment, but one can easily swap Gnome for i3 or another desktop environment, or leave it all together.
This is the procedure I used for installing Arch on a Thinkpad t460s, t490s and a Dell Precision 5550.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;wifi&#34;&gt;Wifi&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;iwctl
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# inside iwctl:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;device list             &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# ge.g., wlan0&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;station wlan0 scan
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;station wlan0 get-networks
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;6&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;station wlan0 connect &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;your-SSID&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
